{"content_excerpt":"# Pipeline Config\n\n> Generated by `/scan`. Populate Agents table with detected subprojects.\n\n## Pipeline Phases\n\nCanonical vocabulary: `ANALYZE → PLAN → EXECUTE → REVIEW → QA → CLOSE`\n(+ `COORDINATE` for roadmaps / multi-spec parents).\nSingle source of truth — phase names, descriptions, entry triggers: `refs/canonical-phases.md`.\n\n### Spec Artifact — Two Layers\n\nA spec is a single `spec.md` file organized in two named layers:\n\n- `## PRD` — the *what & why* (intent): `## Contexto`, `## Usuários/Stakeholders`, `## Métrica de sucesso`, `## Não-Objetivos`, closing with `## Critérios de Aceitação` (the verifiable *what*).\n- `## Plano` — the *how* (execution): `## Informações da Entidade`, `## Arquivos`, optional `## Component Contract`, `## Tarefas`, `## Dependências`, `## Limites`.\n\nBoth `## PRD` and `## Plano` are `##`-level **divider headings**; every parsed subsection stays at `##` (parsers anchor on `## Contexto`, `## Arquivos`, `## Tarefas`, `## Critérios de Aceitação`, `## Limites`). PLAN produces both layers; `/approve` approves them together (no separate PRD gate); EXECUTE consumes the Plano layer; QA runs the Critérios de Aceitação. Light scope keeps the same two-layer shape but lean. Heading templates: `/feature` § Full/Light Scope and `refs/feature/spec-language.md`.\n\n## Agents\n| Color | Role | Subproject | Build Command | Validate Command |\n|-------|------|-----------|---------------|------------------|\n<!-- Populated by /scan from detected subprojects -->\n\n## Role Rules\n| Role | Boundary | Return Sections |\n|------|----------|-----------------|\n| api | Server-side modules. NEVER schemas or UI | Files, Endpoints, Build, Guards Verified |\n| mobile | Flutter/Dart app. NEVER native or backend | Files, Screens, Analysis, Guards Verified |\n| ui | Interfaces with type safety. NEVER API or schemas | Files, Components, Routes, Type-check, Guards Verified |\n| database | Schema and migrations only. NEVER business logic | Files, Migrations, Build, Guards Verified |\n| library | Shared code. NEVER UI or API endpoints | Files, Exports, Build, Guards Verified |\n\n## Wave Transitions\n<!-- Populated by /scan based on detected dependencies -->\n### After: api → Before: ui,mobile\n1. Restart backend (if applicable)\n2. Regenerate types (if applicable)\n\n## Compact Guidance\n\nStrategic `/compact` suggestions to optimize context window usage during pipeline execution.\n\n**When to suggest `/compact`:**\n- After ANALYZE phase completes (especially if >8 file reads or >3 Grep searches were needed)\n- After a debugging/retry loop with >2 retries in EXECUTE phase\n- After an agent wave completes and before starting the next wave\n- After a failed approach is abandoned, before trying an alternative\n\n**When NOT to suggest `/compact`:**\n- Mid-implementation (variable names, file paths, and partial state would be lost)\n- During active agent execution\n- When context usage is below 50%\n\n**Format:** Present as an advisory suggestion, never block or auto-compact:\n> \"Heavy analysis complete. Consider running `/compact` before EXECUTE to optimize context window. Then use `/resume` to continue.\"\n\n## Skill Discovery Heuristic\n\n**Regra**: Se um SKILL faz glob + parse + agregação de filesystem state e devolve uma tabela determinística, isso é trabalho de `mustard-rt`, não do LLM.\n\n**Critério decisor**: A operação muda com estado do disco/SQLite, ou com decisão humana?\n- Só estado do disco/SQLite → mora num subcomando `mustard-rt run <X>`.\n- Decisão humana (judgment, prosa, prioridade) → fica no LLM.\n\n**Sinais de violação no SKILL.md** (telltale phrases):\n- `Glob \\`.claude/...\\`` seguido de iteração\n- `For each {spec|skill|entity|wave}...` para extrair campos estruturados\n- `Parse YAML frontmatter` linha-a-linha\n- `Iterate \\`registry.e\\``\n- `read .* lines` repetido por arquivo\n- Renderização de tabela markdown a partir de N arquivos do filesystem\n\n**Padrão correto**:\n1. SKILL chama UM comando: `rtk mustard-rt run <subcomando> --format table`.\n2. SKILL imprime a saída verbatim.\n3. SKILL embute blocos ESTÁT... [truncated, 22493 bytes more]","file_path":"C:\\Atiz\\mustard\\.claude\\pipeline-config.md","tool":"Read","tool_use_id":"toolu_014hGuQWFbE76wGG5MDQ8P6R"}